column5: I agree that our country has wasted vast amounts of money, not just in resources of man power, or the judicial system, and the prison system, in keeping pot unlawful, but as history has shown, prohibition does not work! It makes a black market that is un-controllable, a cost that is un-sustainable, and makes criminals of many people that should not be! I have personally seen reference books in a public library that stated such crazt things as, a person high on pot could kill their entire family because of paranoia, or that a person high on pot might walk up to a curb and be afraid to step off because they thought it was a cliff and they would fall to their death, or that a person high on pot could walk through a room full of broken glass and feel no pain! Please these are or were reference books in a public library! Obviously propaganda! I can\'t believe that a reasonably prudent person nowadays could possibly believe any of that drivel! We waste more money and time trying to impose a particular belief on society that is totally BS than it could possibly be worth no matter what! Wake up! At least most of the medical profession has! WE are WASTING TO MUCH TIME and MONEY ON THIS!
